---
name: req-type-collision-smoke-fixture
---
[route, serve, Response, Request](std/http.ssc)

```scalascript
// A DOMAIN `Request` collides on the NAME with the http `Request` (different
// shape/arity). v1 tolerates this via dynamic by-name field lookup; v2 must
// resolve each field access against the layout matching the receiver's arity
// (v2-req-form-type-collision). This is exactly busi's hub: http `Request`
// (routes) + domain `Request` (../domain/requests.ssc) in one file.
case class Request(id: String, kind: String)
val demo = Request("r1", "task")

// http Request field access WITH an arg (req.params("x")) must still resolve,
// AND the domain Request's own fields (demo.id/demo.kind) must resolve.
route("GET", "/mid/:x/tail") { req =>
  Response(200, Map(), "mid=" + req.params("x") + " id=" + demo.id + " kind=" + demo.kind)
}
route("GET", "/end/:x") { req => Response(200, Map(), "end=" + req.params("x")) }
serve(8834)
```
